HEADWORD: mocker nut
<hw>mocker nut</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <def>A smooth-barked North American
hickory (<spn>Carya tomentosa</spn>) with 7 to 9 leaflets bearing a
hard-shelled edible nut, which is far inferior to the true shagbark
hickory nut.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mockernut hickory, black hickory, white-heart
hickory, big-bud hickory, <spn>Carya tomentosa</spn> .</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The fruit of the mockernut{1}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mockery</ent>⟦br⟧
